stence rather than direct conversion of 2-aminoimidazole to histidine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_005", "rxn_007", "rxn_009", "rxn_006", "rxn_008", "rxn_011", "rxn_012", "rxn_013"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_011", "mol_013", "mol_010", "mol_007", "mol_012"]}, {"pathway_id": "P8", "name": "Purine-linked heterocycle coexistence pathway into direct Shen-Or\u00f3 core", "description": "HCN oligomerization generates adenine and AIC-like compounds in the same cyanide pool that also supplies formamidine for the direct histidine pathway. This pathway emphasizes molecular convergence of purine and histidine imidazole chemistry without unsupported salvage interconversion.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_005", "rxn_010", "rxn_006", "rxn_008", "rxn_011", "rxn_012", "rxn_013"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_014", "mol_015", "mol_010", "mol_007", "mol_012"]}, {"pathway_id": "P9", "name": "Hydrothermal-surface-biochemical fully connected pathway", "description": "Hydrothermal CO2 reduction generates reduced carbon feedstocks, surface atmospheric chemistry generates HCN, surface wet-dry chemistry builds erythrose and the imidazole aldehyde, and biochemical pool hydrolysis yields histidine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_003", "rxn_005", "rxn_006", "rxn_008", "rxn_011", "rxn_012", "rxn_013"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_003", "mol_004", "mol_005", "mol_008", "mol_012", "mol_016"]}, {"pathway_id": "P10", "name": "Histidine-to-histidyl-histidine elaboration pathway", "description": "The validated Shen-Or\u00f3 route yields histidine, which is then further condensed with cyanamide in prebiotic pools to form a catalytic dipeptide, illustrating downstream functional elaboration.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_005", "rxn_006", "rxn_008", "rxn_011", "rxn_012", "rxn_013", "rxn_014"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_010", "mol_007", "mol_012", "mol_017", "mol_018"]}], "hub_molecules": ["mol_004", "mol_005", "mol_007", "mol_008", "mol_012"], "convergence_points": [{"molecule_id": "mo